# Default Trivy ignore configuration for CI pipelines.
# Projects can override this by placing their own .trivyignore in the project root.
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#by-finding-ids
#
# Format: Add finding IDs (one per line) to suppress known false positives.
# Example:
#   AVD-DS-0002
#   AVD-KSV-0001
